and his lands if he were not?

306
00:16:52,850 --> 00:16:53,880
Hear, hear!

307
00:16:53,890 --> 00:16:56,710
The men of Jinnouchi  must be strong!

308
00:16:56,730 --> 00:17:01,020
After all, we of the Jinnouchi were once
soldiers of the awe-inspiring Takeda army!

309
00:17:01,030 --> 00:17:01,810
Here he goes again.

310
00:17:01,820 --> 00:17:06,500
After Takeda's army was defeated his
retainers scattered to the four winds,

311
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:09,450
and our once glorious
 past was in shambles.

312
00:17:09,450 --> 00:17:14,000
But our ancestors fought
 bravely in many wars

313
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,000
to hold the land  they'd found in Ueda.

314
00:17:18,130 --> 00:17:20,900
August 2nd, 1585!

315
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:23,450
Just 2000 of  our ancestors

316
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:26,960
clashed against 7000
 of Tokugawa's elite!

317
00:17:26,970 --> 00:17:28,750
That was  the first battle of Ueda!

318
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,200
Right in one!

319
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:33,100
It was a crafty,  wily war!

320
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:36,350
The enemy thrust forth into
the center of the village,

321
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:37,750
and there our ancestors took
advantage of the terrain,

322
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:39,580
driving the enemy to
the river's banks...

323
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:44,900
Turn around.

324
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:51,070
Why did I have to lose that
game of rock-paper-scissors?

325
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:54,600
I have to admit I'm jealous.
Pretending to be her boyfriend, huh?

326
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:56,750
There's nothing  to be
jealous of. It's just a job.

327
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:58,800
So come on,  how is it? Fun?

328
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:01,280
I'm surrounded by strangers.  It's hard.

329
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:03,100
Oh, sure. As if.

330
00:18:03,100 --> 00:18:07,200
You're sleeping under the same roof as
Natsuki-sempai, the prettiest girl in school!

331
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:11,000
Since you're pretending to be her boyfriend anyway,
you might as well ask to share the same room.

332
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,600
Wh-what?!

333
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,600
There's no way that'd fly!

334
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:16,300
Well, best of luck.

335
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:22,650
Huh? Where am I?

336
00:18:25,820 --> 00:18:28,730
Now that I look at it,
this is one big house.

337
00:18:40,580 --> 00:18:41,600
What do you want?

338
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:43,620
Uhh, I'm just a little lost.

339
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,660
The bathroom's  around
the corner to your right.

340
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:47,620
Thanks.

341
00:18:49,970 --> 00:18:52,900
Shouldn't you  be with everyone else?

342
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:02,890
Mommy!

343
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:05,810
You haven't toweled off yet.

344
00:19:05,910 --> 00:19:06,970
Kana...

345
00:19:09,490 --> 00:19:10,730

S-s-sorry!

346
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:13,550
The bathroom's free. 
You should take a bath.

347
00:19:13,550 --> 00:19:17,340
No, I, that is, I don't
need to, not today, umm...

348
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:29,700
Natsuki-sempai's  been in this tub...

349
00:19:36,430 --> 00:19:38,400
- It was a tie! 
- A tie!

350
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,300
Hayate, it's me.

351
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:45,600
Have you forgotten me?

352
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:49,470
Why are you here?

353
00:19:50,110 --> 00:19:52,380
What do you mean by
that?  This is my home.

354
00:19:52,530 --> 00:19:53,800
Like hell  it is!

355
00:19:55,410 --> 00:19:57,600
Fiery as ever,  aren't
you, Mariko-obasan.

356
00:19:57,870 --> 00:19:59,450
Things haven't changed a
bit since ten years ago.

357
00:19:59,450 --> 00:20:01,150
The same goes for you.

358
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:03,300
Is that any  way to act,

359
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:04,500
showing your face for the
first time in a decade?

360
00:20:05,130 --> 00:20:06,700
What's the  occasion?

361
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,400
The birthday  celebration is on Sunday.

362
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:10,700
Whose?

363
00:20:16,260 --> 00:20:17,000
Wabisuke.

364
00:20:17,430 --> 00:20:18,250
Wabisuke?

365
00:20:20,770 --> 00:20:23,200
Hey, granny.  Still alive?

366
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:26,750
I should say the same. I was worried
you'd had an accident somewhere.

367
00:20:28,020 --> 00:20:30,850
That attitude would keep
you breathing past a hundred.

368
00:20:30,850 --> 00:20:31,750
Have you...

369
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:34,520
had anything to eat?

370
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:36,950
I'm not hungry.

371
00:20:37,820 --> 00:20:40,190
Japan's really  a bore.

372
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:43,050
Humid and  hot summer,

373
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:45,450
narrow roads,

374
00:20:45,460 --> 00:20:47,000
and full to bursting  with people.

375
00:20:55,340 --> 00:20:57,040
But at least the  beer's great.

376
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:00,600
Ojisan?

377
00:21:03,310 --> 00:21:04,760
Wabisuke-ojisan!

378
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:06,760
Natsuki?

379
00:21:07,230 --> 00:21:08,260
Is that you, Natsuki?

380
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:10,400
Awesome!  You came back!

381
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:13,050
Natsuki!  Let go of him.

382
00:21:13,060 --> 00:21:16,100
Why?  Come on...

383
00:21:19,530 --> 00:21:21,100
It's already been a decade, huh.

384
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:23,070
Like they say, time flies.

385
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:26,060
Umm... who is  Wabisuke-san, exactly?

386
00:21:26,070 --> 00:21:28,060
You've never met him
before, have you, Nana-chan?

387
00:21:28,070 --> 00:21:29,700
It's a complicated story.

388
00:21:29,710 --> 00:21:32,750
It's not complicated
 at all. He's family.

389
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:35,800
Long story short he's the
son of Grandfather's mistress.

390
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:36,830
Really?

391
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:39,460
It was commonplace 
back in the old days.

392
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:42,790
He sold the deed  to
Grandma's mountains,

393
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:46,090
took the money and  ran
all the way to America!

394
00:21:46,730 --> 00:21:48,470
He's a horrible,  selfish man.

395
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:50,750
Really?

396
00:21:50,750 --> 00:21:52,140
You haven't  married yet?

397
00:21:52,140 --> 00:21:53,650
Then, do you have a girlfriend?

398
00:21:53,940 --> 00:21:55,250
Why would  you want to know?

399
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:56,450
Great.

400
00:21:56,490 --> 00:21:57,870
I'll come visit  you in America soon.

401
00:21:57,870 --> 00:21:59,430
You can take me  to the Disney resorts.

402
00:21:59,430 --> 00:22:01,940
First California,  then Florida.

403
00:22:01,950 --> 00:22:04,400
And then we'll go back  to your place.

404
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:06,400
Give me your phone
number so I can call you.

405
00:22:06,410 --> 00:22:07,700
If you win.

406
00:22:07,710 --> 00:22:09,240
Huh? Come on!

407
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:10,700
That's more fun, isn't it?

408
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,260
Fine...

409
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:13,330
Hah!

410
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:17,330
3 bright! There you go.

411
00:22:17,340 --> 00:22:18,460
Want to stop?

412
00:22:20,510 --> 00:22:21,080
Not yet.

413
00:22:21,080 --> 00:22:22,350
Koi koi!

414
00:22:22,350 --> 00:22:24,210
I see. Then, my turn.

415
00:22:26,730 --> 00:22:28,340
Going for 4 bright, hmm?

416
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:29,800
N-not really...

417
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:32,500
What a shame!

418
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:34,140
3 plain.

419
00:22:34,140 --> 00:22:35,020
Ah, koi koi?

420
00:22:35,030 --> 00:22:35,650
Nope.

421
00:22:35,690 --> 00:22:36,930
Come on!

422
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:38,650
I win.

423
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:40,840
Now, time for  you kids to go to bed.

424
00:22:40,850 --> 00:22:42,450
I don't wanna.  One more?

425
00:22:42,450 --> 00:22:44,360
I like to  cut and run.

426
00:22:44,580 --> 00:22:45,320
Take it from here.

427
00:22:45,700 --> 00:22:46,990
I haven't figured  out the rules yet...

428
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:48,900
Hey, how long are you going to stay?

429
00:22:49,580 --> 00:22:50,450
Dunno.

430
00:22:51,210 --> 00:22:52,660
Just don't leave at all!

431
00:22:52,750 --> 00:22:54,120
Right? Got it?

432
00:23:08,430 --> 00:23:10,550
What am I  doing here?

433
00:23:18,490 --> 00:23:20,350
<i>Text message</i>

434
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,190
What is this?

435
00:24:11,620 --> 00:24:12,650
Got it!

436
00:24:15,290 --> 00:24:17,080
<i>Message sent</i>

437
00:24:31,930 --> 00:24:33,180
What was that?

438
00:24:57,750 --> 00:24:59,920
Let's see how she's doing...

439
00:25:00,420 --> 00:25:02,160
<i>Blood Pressure  Heartbeat</i>

440
00:25:08,350 --> 00:25:09,750
- Get up! 
- Get up!

441
00:25:12,470 --> 00:25:13,600
Wake up already!

442
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,090
Get uuup!

443
00:25:15,090 --> 00:25:17,840
The damage is quite extensive, yes.

444
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:19,390
What what what what what?

445
00:25:19,900 --> 00:25:20,450
Look!

446
00:25:20,450 --> 00:25:22,140
That's him, isn't it?

447
00:25:22,150 --> 00:25:24,140
Dead certain. He's the culprit!

448
00:25:24,860 --> 00:25:27,480
The culprit is a minor? A student!?

449
00:25:27,610 --> 00:25:29,700
Now, the more I look at him,
the younger he seems to be.

450
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:31,400
He must be a high schooler, right?

451
00:25:31,990 --> 00:25:33,280
That's...

452
00:25:33,790 --> 00:25:34,530
that's me!

453
00:25:34,750 --> 00:25:38,910
This young man has managed to infiltrate
OZ's system and plunge it into chaos.

454
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:40,250
<i>Current state of OZ</i>

455
00:25:40,250 --> 00:25:42,660
It'll be quite a while until
things are back to normal.

456
00:25:43,460 --> 00:25:46,160
The attack seems to have
been carried out on a whim.

457
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:50,880
A pleasure crime, then. I did notice that
I couldn't read my mail in the morning.

458
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:55,600
You know, there are almost as many OZ
subscribers as there are cell phone users.

459
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:59,720
Since every aspect of everyday life,
from shopping to taking care of business

460
00:25:59,730 --> 00:26:02,810
will be affected by this 
attack, it seems certain that

461
00:26:03,230 --> 00:26:06,560
punishment will be unavoidable even
if it was only a pleasure crime.

462
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:08,400
What's a pleasure crime?

463
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,400
Something that feels good?

464
00:26:10,990 --> 00:26:12,150
What's so funny over there?

465
00:26:12,150 --> 00:26:13,320
Breakfast time!

466
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,110
- Hey! Gimme– 
- No!

467
00:26:20,460 --> 00:26:21,870
Hang on! No! Give me that! Give it back!

468
00:26:22,380 --> 00:26:23,450
Criminal, criminal!

469
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:25,000
Give it to me!

470
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:26,080
He's evil!

471
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:28,460
It's not me!

472
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:31,300
Huh?

473
00:26:33,970 --> 00:26:34,710
Time to eat!

474
00:26:37,850 --> 00:26:39,300
<i>Unable to access the OZ Family network.
You may attempt to log in 2 more times.</i>

475
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:39,300
Huh?

476
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:42,850
<i>Unable to access the OZ Family network.
You may attempt to log in 1 more time.</i>

477
00:26:42,030 --> 00:26:42,850
Huuuh?

478
00:26:42,860 --> 00:26:43,720
Why?

479
00:26:45,730 --> 00:26:46,700
Where was it again...

480
00:26:52,530 --> 00:26:53,400
There!

481
00:26:53,530 --> 00:26:55,100
Are you behind this?

482
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:56,300
Hey, lemme use your PC!

483
00:26:56,620 --> 00:26:57,900
I don't like the way you asked.

484
00:26:57,900 --> 00:27:00,350
Ask like you'd ask  a business partner.

485
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:04,700
Excuse me, but may I please

486
00:27:04,700 --> 00:27:06,500
use your computer for a moment?

487
00:27:08,970 --> 00:27:10,040
Thanks!

488
00:27:15,310 --> 00:27:16,250
Why?

489
00:27:16,310 --> 00:27:17,570
What's wrong?

490
00:27:17,570 --> 00:27:19,880
I think my  account's been hijacked!

491
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,600
So you've been framed, huh.

492
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:22,680
What do I do?

493
00:27:22,810 --> 00:27:24,430
Call customer support.

494
00:27:24,430 --> 00:27:25,140
That's right!

495
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:29,140
Hello? He–

496
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:31,600
Your OZ account has 
not been authenticated,

497
00:27:31,600 --> 00:27:34,150
so you cannot peruse
 your cellular phone.

498
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:36,940
I can't call them!  It won't work!

499
00:27:36,940 --> 00:27:38,230
Calm down.

500
00:27:38,230 --> 00:27:39,190
Koiso-kun.

501
00:27:40,790 --> 00:27:42,030
I told you, calm down.

502
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:45,030
It's a Sakuma-san calling from Tokyo.

503
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:47,250
Don't tell me you're behind this.

504
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:48,120
Of course I'm not!

505
00:27:48,130 --> 00:27:50,410
Figured. You don't have the motive or
the guts to pull off something like this.

506
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:52,540
All right, already! Help me out!

507
00:27:52,550 --> 00:27:53,300
Ain't gonna happen.

508
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:56,450
The password's been changed. I
can't connect to the control sector.

509
00:27:56,470 --> 00:27:58,420
I thought OZ's security was
supposed to be world class!

510
00:27:58,890 --> 00:28:01,720
A strange e-mail was spread
all through OZ yesterday.

511
00:28:01,730 --> 00:28:02,680
A strange e-mail?

512
00:28:03,060 --> 00:28:06,150
OZ's security is locked
 with a 2056 number code.

513
00:28:06,150 --> 00:28:08,430
It can't be hacked  so easily.

514
00:28:08,860 --> 00:28:10,640
But it looks like someone managed
to crack the code in just one night!

515
00:28:11,030 --> 00:28:12,440
2056 numbers?

516
00:28:12,860 --> 00:28:13,980
What's the first number?

517
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:15,050
Eight.

518
00:28:19,330 --> 00:28:20,900
That....  that was me.

519
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:22,110
I solved it.

