00:43:23,860 --> 00:43:27,360
People's lives may  be in danger.

782
00:43:32,530 --> 00:43:34,070
Hello, what's your emergency?

783
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:35,800
Huh? Grandma!

784
00:43:35,800 --> 00:43:37,100
Why're you calling an  emergency number?

785
00:43:37,120 --> 00:43:41,550
Yorihiko! Make sure to 
visit all the elderly! Got it?

786
00:43:42,130 --> 00:43:45,920
Kunihiko! This is no time 
to be lazing about! Move it!

787
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:47,350
Understand, Katsuhiko? This is a battle.

788
00:43:47,350 --> 00:43:51,550
- I'll do what I can. 
- What you can? Huh?

789
00:43:56,850 --> 00:43:58,500
Kan-chan? It's me, Sakae.

790
00:43:58,500 --> 00:44:00,500
It's been a while, hasn't it?

791
00:44:00,500 --> 00:44:04,300
I'm asking as a fellow 
retainer of the Takeda clan:

792
00:44:04,300 --> 00:44:06,880
what kind of emergency
plan is the MLIT setting up?

793
00:44:06,900 --> 00:44:09,400
What? You're just now
planning a meeting to discuss?

794
00:44:09,400 --> 00:44:10,690
Don't give me that bullshit!

795
00:44:10,700 --> 00:44:13,520
Sone-yan? Get some
medical  people together

796
00:44:13,530 --> 00:44:18,400
and help the emergency
workers. Even the retired ones.

797
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:23,050
It's your fool of a son's chance to finally
be some help to the world with that NPO of his.

798
00:44:23,080 --> 00:44:26,000
Itomi-san, it's important
that everyone communicates

799
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:30,270
with one another like the old days.

800
00:44:29,300 --> 00:44:32,420
That's your  specialty, isn't it?

801
00:44:32,420 --> 00:44:34,830
Sen-san, your decisions are
going to be crucial here.

802
00:44:34,850 --> 00:44:36,600
I know it's not easy,

803
00:44:36,600 --> 00:44:38,950
but it's not worth  people's lives.

804
00:44:39,140 --> 00:44:41,200
Don't call me sensei,

805
00:44:41,200 --> 00:44:44,660
just listen to an old  woman's request.

806
00:44:44,690 --> 00:44:47,340
Why're you bringing up
those long gone days, kiddo?

807
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:50,950
It's been half a century
 since I beat you up.

808
00:44:51,570 --> 00:44:54,060
Thousands, no, tens of thousands
of people are in danger.

809
00:44:54,070 --> 00:44:56,720
If you don't step up
now,  then when will you?

810
00:44:56,730 --> 00:44:58,180
Don't give up.

811
00:44:58,200 --> 00:45:00,740
No matter what, you can't give up.

812
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:03,900
This is something  only you can do.

813
00:45:03,900 --> 00:45:06,000
You can do it.

814
00:45:06,170 --> 00:45:07,410
I'm telling you, you can.

815
00:45:07,840 --> 00:45:10,500
Right, that's the spirit.

816
00:45:10,550 --> 00:45:14,000
The man she's talking 
to is the chief of Police.

817
00:45:14,150 --> 00:45:14,930
Incredible.

818
00:45:15,590 --> 00:45:19,450
Everyone's listening
to  what she has to say.

819
00:45:19,460 --> 00:45:22,550
Am I deaf?  Don't get uppity with me.

820
00:45:22,550 --> 00:45:24,500
Check to make sure your dentures
aren't falling out first!

821
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:26,950
I'm not that old yet!

822
00:45:27,820 --> 00:45:30,400
OZ's engineering team
 is out in full force,

823
00:45:30,400 --> 00:45:32,550
but they still haven't even
gotten close to the control sector.

824
00:45:33,490 --> 00:45:35,200
Try and type in something.

825
00:45:35,990 --> 00:45:39,450
An encrypted code should pop up
if you enter the wrong password.

826
00:45:41,040 --> 00:45:43,250
This is a code?

827
00:46:04,140 --> 00:46:06,000
You can do it!

828
00:46:07,940 --> 00:46:09,750
You can!

829
00:46:12,780 --> 00:46:14,480
What the hell is he?

830
00:46:14,490 --> 00:46:16,950
Japan's representative
in the math Olympiads.

831
00:46:16,950 --> 00:46:18,800
Almost, that is.

832
00:46:19,030 --> 00:46:20,140
I'm done!

833
00:46:36,380 --> 00:46:37,250
We're in!

834
00:46:39,090 --> 00:46:40,290
Sad news, Kenji.

835
00:46:40,300 --> 00:46:41,120
Huh?

836
00:46:41,140 --> 00:46:43,010
Looking into the security
logs in the database,

837
00:46:43,010 --> 00:46:46,450
55 people worldwide  managed
to crack the code yesterday,

838
00:46:46,450 --> 00:46:49,800
but your  name isn't among them.

839
00:46:50,400 --> 00:46:51,500
What? Why?

840
00:46:51,770 --> 00:46:55,100
You got the last letter  wrong! BZZZT!

841
00:46:55,110 --> 00:46:57,900
What?  Dammit, you're not the culprit?

842
00:46:58,200 --> 00:47:01,800
But it looks like everyone who sent
in a reply had their avatars stolen.

843
00:47:02,300 --> 00:47:03,900
Hey, cheer up.

844
00:47:04,080 --> 00:47:05,920
You got it right this time.

845
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:11,720
And so, though there was
much confusion nationwide,

846
00:47:11,750 --> 00:47:14,680
thankfully there were no casualties.

847
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:17,120
The trouble was caused by

848
00:47:17,130 --> 00:47:21,450
a system error brought about when two
identical accounts were accidentally generated.

849
00:47:21,800 --> 00:47:27,420
It has been announced,
 however, that it is

850
00:47:27,430 --> 00:47:32,650
technologically impossible to purposely
misuse OZ's system for malicious intent.

851
00:47:36,190 --> 00:47:38,400
Here we are recapping the 10th day of the Nagano
High School Baseball tournament, with Ueda High...

852
00:47:42,530 --> 00:47:43,700
Everyone quiet down a moment!

853
00:47:45,080 --> 00:47:49,500
Though both teams scored many
runs in the final innings,

854
00:47:49,500 --> 00:47:51,370
Ueda High defeated  Sakuchousei High

855
00:47:51,380 --> 00:47:53,110
and has advanced to the
finals, to be held tomorrow.

856
00:47:53,130 --> 00:47:54,600
- Great! 
- Hooray!

857
00:47:55,170 --> 00:47:57,950
Beats me how they managed to win
letting 30 hits through, though.

858
00:47:58,090 --> 00:47:59,200
It's a miracle!

859
00:47:59,220 --> 00:48:01,920
You can tell when he thinks he's gonna
lose. It's written all over his face.

860
00:48:01,930 --> 00:48:03,440
Like father, like son, eh?

861
00:48:05,180 --> 00:48:06,930
Natsuki, what about  your mom and dad?

862
00:48:07,600 --> 00:48:09,850
Dad's pulling an all-nighter
with repairs on the water pipes.

863
00:48:10,060 --> 00:48:11,450
Mom's still  in Saitama.

864
00:48:11,450 --> 00:48:14,150
She's staying the night
at a business hotel.

865
00:48:14,150 --> 00:48:16,150
I see. That's good.

866
00:48:16,190 --> 00:48:19,900
It's all thanks to Grandma
 giving everyone orders

867
00:48:19,950 --> 00:48:21,900
that this whole thing
 calmed down quickly.

868
00:48:21,950 --> 00:48:23,940
Right, Grandma?

869
00:48:23,950 --> 00:48:26,280
I never gave  anyone orders.

870
00:48:26,290 --> 00:48:27,650
Oh, come on!

871
00:48:28,370 --> 00:48:29,700
Our Grandma's great!

872
00:48:29,710 --> 00:48:30,980
Japan's best!

873
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:35,200
You rascals.

874
00:48:34,750 --> 00:48:37,850
Kenji-san, I hear you stepped
up to the occasion today as well.

875
00:48:38,420 --> 00:48:40,500
No, I...  I didn't really...

876
00:48:40,840 --> 00:48:42,000
Natsuki's boyfriend?

877
00:48:42,010 --> 00:48:44,040
He's not her boyfriend!

878
00:48:44,050 --> 00:48:45,290
I hear he fixed  the problem with OZ.

879
00:48:45,300 --> 00:48:47,200
I thought he was still a high schooler!

880
00:48:47,200 --> 00:48:48,760
Not bad, boyfriend.

881
00:48:48,770 --> 00:48:50,250
I'm telling you, he ain't her boyfriend!

882
00:48:50,270 --> 00:48:51,630
What do you care about it?

883
00:48:51,630 --> 00:48:55,000
And now for an update on the OZ
incident which took place this morning.

884
00:48:55,730 --> 00:48:57,600
Though the system has been restored,

885
00:48:57,600 --> 00:49:01,400
over 2 million accounts in  Japan alone

886
00:49:01,400 --> 00:49:04,150
are still inaccessible.

887
00:49:04,700 --> 00:49:06,730
Though the cause is not  yet clear,

888
00:49:06,740 --> 00:49:09,750
the government has advised all OZ users
to take care in managing their accounts.

889
00:49:08,300 --> 00:49:09,900
What is it?

890
00:49:08,980 --> 00:49:09,900
It's about OZ...

891
00:49:12,250 --> 00:49:13,150
But...

892
00:49:13,170 --> 00:49:15,400
Love Machine  hasn't been beaten yet.

893
00:49:15,710 --> 00:49:16,700
That's right.

894
00:49:16,700 --> 00:49:17,790
Love Machine?

895
00:49:17,800 --> 00:49:19,300
What's that? Morning Musume?

896
00:49:19,300 --> 00:49:21,250
An A.I. that steals accounts.

897
00:49:21,840 --> 00:49:23,040
- What? 
- Let's see.

898
00:49:23,590 --> 00:49:25,000
It's got  a creepy avatar.

899
00:49:25,010 --> 00:49:27,130
Has bad guy written all over him.

900
00:49:27,140 --> 00:49:29,130
So this thing's behind all
the stuff that happened today.

901
00:49:29,640 --> 00:49:31,400
But why wasn't this
reported in the news?

902
00:49:31,980 --> 00:49:33,750
I think it's just a
matter of time, Master.

903
00:49:34,270 --> 00:49:35,600
The Internet's everywhere,

904
00:49:35,600 --> 00:49:37,950
and the people who've noticed what's
going on are already talking about it.

905
00:49:38,730 --> 00:49:42,200
If we pool our knowledge and
resources, we should be able to stop it.

906
00:49:44,360 --> 00:49:46,750
Sorry, but that's  not gonna happen.

907
00:49:55,920 --> 00:49:57,700
How do you know that?

908
00:49:57,710 --> 00:50:00,250
How? Well...

909
00:50:02,170 --> 00:50:05,100
I'm the one who developed  that thing.

910
00:50:07,930 --> 00:50:10,600
You made Love Machine?

911
00:50:10,970 --> 00:50:11,950
Yeah.

912
00:50:12,350 --> 00:50:15,500
It's a hacking A.I. that I designed.

913
00:50:41,340 --> 00:50:43,150
I just did one thing.

914
00:50:43,590 --> 00:50:46,500
I gave a machine the urge  to know.

915
00:50:46,500 --> 00:50:51,000
Then the military of
some country  came to me,

916
00:50:51,260 --> 00:50:54,050
and asked me to sell it to them
so they could run some tests.

917
00:50:57,190 --> 00:51:00,150
I didn't think those tests would  be OZ.

918
00:51:00,690 --> 00:51:01,720
Doesn't matter, I guess.

919
00:51:01,720 --> 00:51:03,750
The results are outstanding.

920
00:51:03,780 --> 00:51:05,650
That thing's urge to know

921
00:51:05,650 --> 00:51:08,400
will make it keep collecting information
and authority from across the world.

922
00:51:08,700 --> 00:51:12,600
As of now, Love Machine holds the
same power as an army millions strong.

923
00:51:13,290 --> 00:51:16,000
Got it? That's  why you can't win.

924
00:51:18,750 --> 00:51:20,740
Do you know how many 
people were hurt today?

925
00:51:21,130 --> 00:51:23,400
Do you know how much
 confusion was caused?

926
00:51:23,630 --> 00:51:24,610
You're saying it's my fault?

927
00:51:24,630 --> 00:51:26,550
Of course not. The A.I. did it.

928
00:51:26,590 --> 00:51:29,340
The world's in chaos  because of you!

929
00:51:29,380 --> 00:51:31,200
You guys just don't get it, do you.

930
00:51:31,300 --> 00:51:34,590
- I said that the A.I.– 
- You really think that makes it okay?

931
00:51:34,600 --> 00:51:35,400
Don't do it.

932
00:51:35,430 --> 00:51:37,200
You're a coward  hiding
behind that excuse!

933
00:51:37,230 --> 00:51:38,300
Calm down!

934
00:51:38,300 --> 00:51:39,100
I'm telling you!

935
00:51:39,390 --> 00:51:44,200
I just developed the damn thing, I never told
the artificial intelligence to do anything!

936
00:51:44,200 --> 00:51:44,400
Shut up!

937
00:51:44,400 --> 00:51:46,200
Stop it! What do you think
you're doing with Grandma here?

938
00:51:49,740 --> 00:51:50,750
Wabisuke.

939
00:51:51,240 --> 00:51:52,850
- What's the hubbub? 
- Ssh!

940
00:51:54,700 --> 00:51:57,070
You understand, right, Grandma?

941
00:52:02,290 --> 00:52:04,700
I'm sorry for all the trouble
I've caused you up to now.

942
00:52:05,000 --> 00:52:07,600
I've been working to 
make it all up to you.

943
00:52:08,220 --> 00:52:11,600
so that I could come back to
this house with my head held high.

944
00:52:15,600 --> 00:52:17,700
Grandma, look at this.

945
00:52:19,890 --> 00:52:22,500
The American military's
given me an official contract.

946
00:52:23,110 --> 00:52:25,390
We're going to get  more money

947
00:52:25,400 --> 00:52:27,000
than even Father managed to earn.

948
00:52:28,280 --> 00:52:30,400
This is all thanks to you, Grandma.

949
00:52:30,650 --> 00:52:35,800
I was able to develop it
with the money you had, see.

950
00:52:41,120 --> 00:52:42,150
Mother!

951
00:52:46,300 --> 00:52:47,000
Run!

952
00:52:56,600 --> 00:52:57,340
Wabisuke!

953
00:52:57,350 --> 00:52:58,830
Pay the price for your crimes!

954
00:53:14,700 --> 00:53:16,100
I shouldn't have come back.

955
00:53:19,660 --> 00:53:20,600
Ojisan!

956
00:53:22,370 --> 00:53:23,320
Natsuki!

957
00:53:24,630 --> 00:53:25,660
Listen up, you all!

958
00:53:25,670 --> 00:53:29,100
We must take care of the
problem caused by one of our own!

959
00:53:52,400 --> 00:53:53,450
Sempai.

960
00:54:01,500 --> 00:54:02,530
Natsuki-sempai.

961
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:05,400
Don't come near me.

962
00:54:07,210 --> 00:54:09,100
I'm not in the mood to talk right now.

963
00:54:25,600 --> 00:54:29,470
These legs of mine just
won't listen to me anymore.

964
00:54:29,480 --> 00:54:31,220
You shouldn't  have
exerted yourself so much.

965
00:54:31,220 --> 00:54:33,200
Thank you.

966
00:54:33,820 --> 00:54:35,400
Then, I'll be going now.

967
00:54:35,990 --> 00:54:38,600
Do you want to play a game of hanafuda?

968
00:54:43,700 --> 00:54:46,550
The whole family used  to play together,

969
00:54:46,550 --> 00:54:49,900
but these days it's hard to find
someone willing to play against me.

970
00:54:50,840 --> 00:54:52,350
You can go first.

971
00:54:52,590 --> 00:54:53,500
Yes, ma'am.

972
00:54:55,380 --> 00:54:59,200
I'm sorry you had to see
that embarrassing spectacle.

973
00:54:59,720 --> 00:55:00,500
It's nothing.

974
00:55:01,050 --> 00:55:03,600
Even Natsuki's  foolishness.

975
00:55:04,140 --> 00:55:05,300
Koi koi.

976
00:55:05,310 --> 00:55:07,100
- Not bad. 
- Thank you.

977
00:55:08,650 --> 00:55:11,800
Now if  I win this round...

978
00:55:11,800 --> 00:55:14,750
You have to have something
on the line to make it fun.

979
00:55:14,750 --> 00:55:16,100
There, koi koi.

980
00:55:17,200 --> 00:55:20,200
All right then... If I win,

981
00:55:21,700 --> 00:55:24,450
I want you to take care of that girl.

982
00:55:27,660 --> 00:55:30,800
She's still too  immature
to be a good fiancee,

983
00:55:31,080 --> 00:55:33,800
but if you can look  past those faults,

984
00:55:33,800 --> 00:55:36,200
I want to ask  you one more time.

985
00:55:37,720 --> 00:55:40,170
Take care  of Natsuki.

986
00:55:44,680 --> 00:55:45,500
I...

987
00:55:46,060 --> 00:55:49,800
I don't yet have that 
kind of faith in myself.

988
00:55:50,650 --> 00:55:52,600
You can do it.

989
00:56:09,250 --> 00:56:12,100
All I can offer is
that  I'll do my best.

990
00:56:16,050 --> 00:56:17,800
I win!

991
00:57:10,770 --> 00:57:12,770
- Oh no! Get over here! 
- I'm coming!

992
00:57:12,780 --> 00:57:13,700
Quickly!

993
00:57:24,320 --> 00:57:25,250
Grandma!

994
00:57:26,660 --> 00:57:27,760
Open your eyes!

995
00:57:28,200 --> 00:57:29,800
Grandma!

996
00:57:29,830 --> 00:57:32,000
Wake up!

997
00:57:32,000 --> 00:57:33,490
Grandma!

998
00:57:35,170 --> 00:57:36,250
Grandma, can you hear us?

999
00:57:36,250 --> 00:57:37,660
Grandma!

1000
00:57:37,670 --> 00:57:38,550
Please wake up!

1001
00:57:43,430 --> 00:57:45,400
- Switch with me. 
- That's enough.

1002
00:57:45,400 --> 00:57:47,150
No, Katsuhiko!  Keep going!

1003
00:57:47,180 --> 00:57:47,960
It's no use.

1004
00:57:47,970 --> 00:57:49,150
Keep going!

1005
00:58:06,320 --> 00:58:07,700
Everyone's here, right?

1006
00:58:10,800 --> 00:58:12,660
5:21 am.

1007
00:58:27,930 --> 00:58:30,900
She was taking  heart medicine.

1008
00:58:31,600 --> 00:58:33,950
I used this to monitor
 the state of her body.

1009
00:58:33,950 --> 00:58:36,700
Her heartbeat, blood
pressure, perspiration.

1010
00:58:36,730 --> 00:58:39,510
An alarm should have rung
if anything went wrong,

1011
00:58:39,520 --> 00:58:42,600
but I stopped receiving
 data last night.

1012
00:58:42,610 --> 00:58:44,680
The trouble in OZ?

1013
00:58:44,690 --> 00:58:47,770
I guess the system manager's ID
was one of the stolen accounts.

1014
00:58:47,780 --> 00:58:50,190
That means she'd  have
lived if not for that!

1015
00:58:50,200 --> 00:58:53,100
No, I think it was just her time to go.

1016
00:58:53,120 --> 00:58:55,100
What? Like hell it was!

1017
00:58:55,660 --> 00:58:57,060
Where's Wabisuke?

1018
00:58:57,210 --> 00:58:59,000
I'll beat the living
daylights out of him!

1019
00:58:59,500 --> 00:59:02,400
I think he took Shouta's
 car and left last night.

1020
00:59:02,420 --> 00:59:04,340
Nobody knows  how to contact him,

1021
00:59:04,340 --> 00:59:06,570
because he's been gone for ten years.

1022
00:59:10,100 --> 00:59:10,800
Damn it!

1023
00:59:19,100 --> 00:59:20,200
Excuse me.

1024
01:00:16,160 --> 01:00:17,150
Stop them.

1025
01:00:21,630 --> 01:00:22,550
The tears...

1026
01:00:27,170 --> 01:00:28,270
Hold me here.

1027
01:00:29,920 --> 01:00:31,150
Make them stop.

1028
01:01:15,430 --> 01:01:19,090
Now for our next item. The
number of people unable to access

1029
01:01:19,100 --> 01:01:22,150
their OZ accounts  since
yesterday's incident

1030
01:01:22,150 --> 01:01:25,070
has reached over 10   million worldwide.

1031
01:01:26,650 --> 01:01:28,480
Has anyone told Ryouhei?

1032
01:01:29,110 --> 01:01:31,200
We decided to wait  until
after tomorrow's match.

1033
01:01:33,030 --> 01:01:33,650
Yeah.

1034
01:01:38,490 --> 01:01:40,280
Today's going to be a busy day.

1035
01:01:40,290 --> 01:01:42,650
Noriko-chan,
Yumi-chan, Nana-chan.

1036
01:01:43,000 --> 01:01:44,500
I'll leave the cooking to you.

1037
01:01:44,540 --> 01:01:47,000
I hope there'll be  enough sake.

1038
01:01:47,040 --> 01:01:49,600
Mansaku,  I want you
to visit the temple,

1039
01:01:49,630 --> 01:01:52,500
and Yorihiko, I want you and your
brothers to tell the neighbors and guests,

1040
01:01:52,510 --> 01:01:55,000
and find some people
willing to help out.

1041
01:01:56,590 --> 01:01:58,000
Everyone understand?

1042
01:01:58,220 --> 01:02:00,800
Ain't we got more 
important things to do?

1043
01:02:02,350 --> 01:02:04,650
That's right, mother! 
The birthday dumplings!

1044
01:02:04,980 --> 01:02:06,900
We've got to change the
order to funeral dumplings.

1045
01:02:06,900 --> 01:02:08,850
To hell with the dumplings!

1046
01:02:08,860 --> 01:02:10,050
We've got to strike back!

1047
01:02:10,060 --> 01:02:13,000
We have to bash that 
machine to bits! Right?

1048
01:02:13,030 --> 01:02:13,890
Honestly, that's enough.

1049
01:02:13,900 --> 01:02:14,600
What?

1050
01:02:14,860 --> 01:02:17,400
You're no help  at all, little brother.

1051
01:02:17,410 --> 01:02:19,690
What does age have  to do with anything?

1052
01:02:19,700 --> 01:02:23,030
We of the Jinnouchi have to raise
our battle standards and fight!

1053
01:02:23,040 --> 01:02:24,700
What's gotten into you, dad?

1054
01:02:24,710 --> 01:02:27,240
We have to hold Grandma's funeral first.

1055
01:02:27,280 --> 01:02:28,350
That's not as important!

1056
01:02:28,380 --> 01:02:30,880
Wouldn't she want us to
fight and avenge her honor?!

1057
01:02:31,630 --> 01:02:32,500
Umm.

1058
01:02:33,470 --> 01:02:34,790
I agree.

1059
01:02:37,180 --> 01:02:40,840
Up till now, we never realized
that what happened in OZ

1060
01:02:40,850 --> 01:02:42,700
could endanger the 
lives of real people.

1061
01:02:42,970 --> 01:02:43,900
He's dangerous.

1062
01:02:43,930 --> 01:02:48,430
Something like what happened
here could happen anywhere else.

1063
01:02:48,730 --> 01:02:52,190
So we, at least,  have to stop him.

1064
01:02:53,780 --> 01:02:55,480
What're you talking about?

1065
01:02:55,480 --> 01:02:58,550
That is, we have to stop any
more people from getting–

1066
01:02:58,570 --> 01:03:01,020
Who're you to be sticking your
nose into our family matters, huh?

1067
01:03:01,030 --> 01:03:02,820
But...

1068
01:03:02,830 --> 01:03:06,000
How can we worry about other
people on a day like this?

1069
01:03:07,540 --> 01:03:08,280
But...

1070
01:03:12,300 --> 01:03:13,750
Well then, everyone!

1071
01:03:16,300 --> 01:03:17,900
I'm ashamed of the lot of you.

1072
01:03:17,930 --> 01:03:20,420
How can you say  you're Jinnouchi men?

1073
01:03:20,430 --> 01:03:24,300
I understand how you feel, father,
but it's about time you acted your age.

1074
01:03:24,350 --> 01:03:28,170
I didn't ask for your opinion.

1075
01:03:26,180 --> 01:03:28,590
I'm sorry.  I shouldn't
have spoken out of turn...

1076
01:03:29,600 --> 01:03:31,390
No, you were right.

1077
01:03:31,400 --> 01:03:34,110
You have to protect 
others to protect yourself.

1078
01:03:34,860 --> 01:03:36,150
Is that the JSDF motto?

1079
01:03:37,070 --> 01:03:40,180
No... it's a line from
"The Seven Samurai."

1080
01:03:40,200 --> 01:03:40,940
Tasuke-ojisan.

1081
01:03:40,950 --> 01:03:41,900
Hmm?

1082
01:03:41,910 --> 01:03:43,540
Do you stock computers  at your store?

1083
01:03:43,540 --> 01:03:44,430
Of course.

1084
01:03:44,450 --> 01:03:46,040
Do you have any better  than this?

1085
01:03:46,040 --> 01:03:47,050
Of course we do.

1086
01:03:49,000 --> 01:03:50,000
Kazuma-kun.

1087
01:03:51,130 --> 01:03:52,950
We need to fight him.

1088
01:03:54,130 --> 01:03:55,200
This is revenge.

1089
01:03:57,300 --> 01:04:00,580
Honestly, that Mansuke. What
in the world was he thinking?

1090
01:04:00,590 --> 01:04:02,350
There aren't any good pictures here.

1091
01:04:02,390 --> 01:04:04,100
Hey, how about this one?

1092
01:04:04,510 --> 01:04:06,420
Ah, this was the one taken
for that one award ceremony.

1093
01:04:06,430 --> 01:04:07,500
That'll do the trick.

1094
01:04:08,100 --> 01:04:09,680
April 1600,

1095
01:04:09,690 --> 01:04:13,060
Tokugawa Hidetada's  army of 38,000

1096
01:04:13,060 --> 01:04:14,800
struck at Ueda Castle.

1097
01:04:15,070 --> 01:04:17,730
Our forces at the time
numbered a paltry 2,000 men.

1098
01:04:17,740 --> 01:04:20,800
Then how did our 
ancestors face this battle?

1099
01:04:21,410 --> 01:04:27,000
After deliberately luring
 the enemy into the castle,

1100
01:04:27,000 --> 01:04:29,450
they closed and locked the
gates, trapping them inside.

1101
01:04:29,450 --> 01:04:32,600
Trapped like rats,  Tokugawa's army

1102
01:04:32,600 --> 01:04:34,500
lost its will to fight
 and was defeated.

1103
01:04:35,300 --> 01:04:37,850
That was the  second siege of Ueda.

1104
01:04:37,880 --> 01:04:39,000
Did that help any?

1105
01:04:39,590 --> 01:04:40,750
That's a good idea.

1106
01:04:41,130 --> 01:04:42,750
Then with that in mind...

1107
01:04:45,310 --> 01:04:46,450
Hello, Sakuma?

1108
01:04:47,100 --> 01:04:49,000
What're you starting now?

1109
01:04:49,770 --> 01:04:50,750
A war.

1110
01:04:51,520 --> 01:04:53,950
Do you think this will do
for the bedside decorations?

1111
01:04:54,560 --> 01:04:55,700
Well, I guess it will do.

1112
01:04:56,230 --> 01:04:59,800
Even though she's passed on,
her face looks so peaceful.

1113
01:05:00,780 --> 01:05:01,800
It does.

1114
01:05:04,530 --> 01:05:05,800
I dunno if this'll fit.

1115
01:05:12,710 --> 01:05:14,400
You have things  like this in stock?

1116
01:05:14,960 --> 01:05:17,800
"Electronics store" doesn't
just mean household appliances.

1117
01:05:17,800 --> 01:05:21,200
Actually we sell stuff to schools
and government agencies too.

1118
01:05:21,800 --> 01:05:24,670
This was actually 
slated for a university.

1119
01:05:24,670 --> 01:05:26,500
Is it okay to use it?

1120
01:05:26,760 --> 01:05:29,900
It's fine. We're just 
borrowing it for a bit.

1121
01:05:30,930 --> 01:05:32,650
But why did he  suddenly decide on this?

1122
01:05:32,650 --> 01:05:36,650
It's all thanks to you standing
up to the women, Kenji-kun.

1123
01:05:37,020 --> 01:05:39,100
Kazuma must've  seen
that as a motivator.

1124
01:05:39,530 --> 01:05:41,640
The women of our  clan
are strong and assertive,

1125
01:05:41,640 --> 01:05:43,070
so the menfolk  tend to be more passive.

1126
01:05:43,610 --> 01:05:45,500
Now I need a source of electricity...

1127
01:05:54,210 --> 01:05:55,450
Outta the way!

1128
01:06:01,970 --> 01:06:03,470
Great, isn't it? This is my boat.

1129
01:06:03,470 --> 01:06:05,700
Takes 2 hours to  get here from Niigata.

1130
01:06:05,930 --> 01:06:08,250
It can put out up  to 300 kilowatts!

1131
01:06:08,250 --> 01:06:10,010
Watch out, you two.

1132
01:06:10,060 --> 01:06:11,250
I'm gonna  dunk it.

1133
01:06:24,740 --> 01:06:25,900
Incredible.

1134
01:06:30,200 --> 01:06:31,300
What is this?

1135
01:06:31,700 --> 01:06:33,900
A military-grade  antenna module.

1136
01:06:34,330 --> 01:06:36,700
Borrowed it from the
American base in Matsumoto.

1137
01:06:37,210 --> 01:06:39,990
What exactly do you  do
in the JSDF, Riichi-san?

1138
01:06:43,510 --> 01:06:45,500
That's classified.

1139
01:06:46,050 --> 01:06:48,290
What's gotten  into those men?

1140
01:06:49,430 --> 01:06:52,210
- It's a big jeep! 
- Look outside!

1141
01:06:52,220 --> 01:06:53,250
Don't make such a commotion!

1142
01:06:54,480 --> 01:06:56,050
Behave yourselves, children.

1143
01:06:56,310 --> 01:06:57,650
Okay.

1144
01:06:59,560 --> 01:07:02,000
Is it all right for us to
 just sit around like this?

1145
01:07:02,000 --> 01:07:04,100
It's the mourning period.  Calm down.

1146
01:07:04,100 --> 01:07:05,530
3 days is a bit too long for my tastes.

1147
01:07:05,540 --> 01:07:08,300
I keep thinking  about my work.

1148
01:07:08,300 --> 01:07:10,050
Forget that for now.

1149
01:07:10,050 --> 01:07:11,150
That's not going to work.

1150
01:07:11,160 --> 01:07:14,830
Grandma always told us to
help those in need, didn't she?

1151
01:07:14,830 --> 01:07:15,450
That's right.

1152
01:07:15,460 --> 01:07:17,930
Everyone! Please  listen to me!

1153
01:07:22,460 --> 01:07:23,400
Yummy.

1154
01:07:23,400 --> 01:07:26,000
Can't you help a little too, Naomi-san?

1155
01:07:26,380 --> 01:07:28,450
I can't make food  this good.

1156
01:07:29,550 --> 01:07:30,250
What time is it?

1157
01:07:30,800 --> 01:07:31,500
It's time!

1158
01:07:32,810 --> 01:07:33,800
Yumi-san!

1159
01:07:38,350 --> 01:07:40,150
Kazuma!  Change your clothes, will you?

1160
01:07:40,150 --> 01:07:41,050
Later.

1161
01:07:41,690 --> 01:07:44,100
Kazuma-kun looks like
he's  really King Kazma.

1162
01:07:44,400 --> 01:07:47,100
That child used  to be quite weak.

1163
01:07:48,280 --> 01:07:50,520
He learned Shaolin kung fu from his

1164
01:07:50,530 --> 01:07:53,500
grandfather Mansuke  in Niigata
through OZ all the way from Nagoya.

1165
01:07:53,830 --> 01:07:55,450
So that's why he  called him Master.

1166
01:07:59,960 --> 01:08:00,900
Don't touch anything!

1167
01:08:01,250 --> 01:08:02,600
I mean it!

1168
01:08:02,630 --> 01:08:03,790
We're not touching nothing!

1169
01:08:03,800 --> 01:08:05,210
We're just looking!

1170
01:08:05,670 --> 01:08:07,400
Keeping it cool's gonna be the problem.

1171
01:08:07,670 --> 01:08:09,150
We don't have an air conditioner.

1172
01:08:09,550 --> 01:08:11,930
I've got lots of ice in the boat.

1173
01:08:11,970 --> 01:08:12,800
Follow me.

1174
01:08:13,430 --> 01:08:14,900
LCD's response times are too slow.

1175
01:08:15,260 --> 01:08:17,240
Do you have any  HD CRT monitors?

1176
01:08:17,810 --> 01:08:19,000
Course I do.

1177
01:08:23,610 --> 01:08:25,450
Just what kind of people is
Natsuki-sempai's family made of?

1178
01:08:25,650 --> 01:08:26,720
We're just a normal civilian family.

1179
01:08:26,730 --> 01:08:29,440
A 200 teraFLOPS supercomputer,

1180
01:08:29,450 --> 01:08:31,600
and a 100 gig military-grade
 connection line.

1181
01:08:31,600 --> 01:08:34,020
You're telling me that a normal
family has that kinda stuff?

1182
01:08:34,330 --> 01:08:35,550
I want to send a challenge.

1183
01:08:35,990 --> 01:08:37,000
A challenge?

1184
01:08:37,450 --> 01:08:39,010
Sent by  King Kazma.

1185
01:08:39,020 --> 01:08:42,100
"Don't expect it to
be  so easy this time."

1186
01:08:42,100 --> 01:08:43,900
And how do you know that?

1187
01:08:44,460 --> 01:08:46,330
Because I'm King Kazma.

1188
01:08:46,550 --> 01:08:47,750
Tell me another one.

1189
01:08:51,130 --> 01:08:52,200
Wait, really?

1190
01:08:52,260 --> 01:08:53,600
<i>Challenge</i>

1191
01:08:53,600 --> 01:08:55,840
<i>Come to the OZ Coliseum today
at noon (JST). King Kazma</i>

1192
01:09:00,100 --> 01:09:00,830
Master.

1193
01:09:02,060 --> 01:09:03,500
Do you think I can win?

1194
01:09:03,500 --> 01:09:05,140
You're all grown up now.

1195
01:09:05,190 --> 01:09:07,300
You can decide the  outcome by yourself.

1196
01:09:07,650 --> 01:09:09,310
Grown up? But I'm only in middle school.

1197
01:09:09,320 --> 01:09:11,650
You'll be a big brother soon.

1198
01:09:11,820 --> 01:09:13,530
I didn't choose to be.

1199
01:09:13,780 --> 01:09:15,330
And a little sister at that...

1200
01:09:15,620 --> 01:09:18,000
It's not so bad  having siblings.

1201
01:09:18,000 --> 01:09:19,900
Even though you steal
each other's snacks,

1202
01:09:19,900 --> 01:09:21,210
fight every day,

1203
01:09:21,210 --> 01:09:24,900
get sick of even  seeing their faces...

1204
01:09:26,500 --> 01:09:27,550
One minute left!

1205
01:09:28,130 --> 01:09:28,950
I'm ready.

1206
01:09:28,950 --> 01:09:30,160
Me too.

1207
01:09:30,170 --> 01:09:31,160
We can win this time.

1208
01:09:31,470 --> 01:09:32,500
Grit your teeth.

1209
01:09:36,680 --> 01:09:37,800
Let's go together.

1210
01:09:39,350 --> 01:09:40,600
The finals are now beginning.

1211
01:09:40,600 --> 01:09:42,620
Ueda High is up against the
favorites Matsushou Academy!

1212
01:09:42,630 --> 01:09:45,300
If Ueda High can win this
 match, they'll advance

1213
01:09:45,300 --> 01:09:49,730
to the nationals for the
first  time in 24 years.

1214
01:09:49,730 --> 01:09:51,770
But Matsushou's quite strong.

1215
01:09:51,780 --> 01:09:55,150
Will Ueda be  able to pull it off?

1216
01:09:55,160 --> 01:09:59,110
Grandma, please watch  over Ryouhei!

1217
01:09:59,740 --> 01:10:01,900
And we're just  about to start!

1218
01:10:38,820 --> 01:10:39,950
He came!

1219
01:10:55,380 --> 01:10:56,290
Yeah!

1220
01:10:56,340 --> 01:10:57,900
He's fast...  he's really fast!

1221
01:11:15,570 --> 01:11:16,730
I can do it.

1222
01:11:25,960 --> 01:11:26,800
Don't let him run!

1223
01:11:26,800 --> 01:11:28,030
Get him to the trap!

1224
01:11:29,750 --> 01:11:31,400
I can take  care of him by myself!

1225
01:12:02,530 --> 01:12:04,480
He's controlling the  stolen avatars.

1226
01:12:04,490 --> 01:12:05,970
He can do  that?

1227
01:12:10,500 --> 01:12:11,990
Don't do it, Kazuma-kun!

1228
01:12:12,000 --> 01:12:12,900
Run!

1229
01:12:30,900 --> 01:12:31,640
Master!

1230
01:12:31,650 --> 01:12:33,600
I'll keep him occupied, run!

1231
01:12:39,530 --> 01:12:40,240
Master!

1232
01:12:40,240 --> 01:12:41,930
I'm fine,  get him to the trap!

1233
01:12:59,760 --> 01:13:00,600
Got him.

1234
01:13:00,630 --> 01:13:01,290
Sakuma!

1235
01:13:01,300 --> 01:13:02,710
Right on schedule!

1236
01:13:59,730 --> 01:14:01,200
We got him, Grandmother!

1237
01:14:01,200 --> 01:14:02,750
Kazuma did it!

1238
01:14:02,750 --> 01:14:04,700
Yorihiko-san's group! It's your turn!

1239
01:14:04,700 --> 01:14:06,350
Leave it to us.

1240
01:14:06,350 --> 01:14:09,200
We've been gaming for 30
years! Don't underestimate us!

1241
01:14:09,200 --> 01:14:11,600
Even though we haven't been
playing as much lately...

1242
01:14:11,620 --> 01:14:14,250
Our skills haven't rusted a bit!

1243
01:14:38,230 --> 01:14:39,350
We did it!

1244
01:14:40,360 --> 01:14:42,120
Is that daddy's avatar?

1245
01:14:42,490 --> 01:14:44,000
I want that one too!

1246
01:14:44,000 --> 01:14:45,310
Papa's awesome!

1247
01:14:45,780 --> 01:14:46,750
Papa...

1248
01:14:47,240 --> 01:14:51,300
Bottom of the eighth, and Ueda
High is giving a stunning show!

1249
01:14:51,300 --> 01:14:52,050
Yumi-san...

1250
01:14:52,830 --> 01:14:54,100
Like a rat in a trap.

1251
01:14:54,120 --> 01:14:56,660
It's just a matter  of time now.

1252
01:14:58,830 --> 01:14:59,800
What's happening?

1253
01:15:16,890 --> 01:15:18,000
What's this?

1254
01:15:18,000 --> 01:15:19,000
Something's wrong with the stage!

1255
01:15:19,020 --> 01:15:20,800
What's going on?

1256
01:15:20,980 --> 01:15:22,600
Tasuke-san, behind you!

1257
01:15:23,480 --> 01:15:24,350
Behind you?

1258
01:15:24,360 --> 01:15:25,800
What?

1259
01:15:27,740 --> 01:15:29,160
Hot!

1260
01:15:30,070 --> 01:15:31,400
It's about to go critical!

1261
01:15:32,370 --> 01:15:33,940
Where'd all the ice go?

1262
01:15:34,330 --> 01:15:36,100
We had lots more than this...

1263
01:15:36,370 --> 01:15:38,240
Shouta-nii took it.

1264
01:15:38,250 --> 01:15:39,700
What?!

1265
01:15:44,800 --> 01:15:46,420
Is that cool enough, Grandma?

1266
01:15:46,760 --> 01:15:49,400
They say today's  the
hottest day of summer.

1267
01:15:52,760 --> 01:15:54,430
Top of the ninth, and Ueda's pitcher

1268
01:15:54,430 --> 01:15:56,600
Jinnouchi is  beginning to crack.

1269
01:15:56,600 --> 01:15:59,300
He looks very tired, doesn't he?

1270
01:15:59,310 --> 01:16:00,540
Ryouhei!

1271
01:16:00,560 --> 01:16:02,150
And Matsushou  continues
their offensive!

1272
01:16:59,750 --> 01:17:01,780
These are all the 
avatars he's absorbed!

1273
01:17:02,000 --> 01:17:03,990
More than 400 million!

1274
01:17:19,270 --> 01:17:20,550
Kazuma-kun, run!

1275
01:17:20,550 --> 01:17:21,720
Kazuma-kun!

1276
01:17:43,750 --> 01:17:46,350
It's so hot that Grandma
 might start to rot,

1277
01:17:46,500 --> 01:17:49,000
and here you guys  are playing games.

1278
01:17:49,960 --> 01:17:50,950
...all because of you...

1279
01:17:51,300 --> 01:17:52,700
Huh? What was that?

1280
01:17:53,130 --> 01:17:54,450
This is all your fault!

1281
01:17:56,140 --> 01:17:57,650
This is because you...!

1282
01:17:57,650 --> 01:17:58,850
Stop, Kazuma-kun!

1283
01:17:59,930 --> 01:18:00,350
What's the deal!

1284
01:18:00,640 --> 01:18:02,020
Are you okay, Shouta-nii?

1285
01:18:02,270 --> 01:18:04,360
Everything's gone to 
hell since you showed up!

1286
01:18:04,360 --> 01:18:05,840
Natsuki getting all weird!

1287
01:18:05,940 --> 01:18:07,100
Grandma died!

1288
01:18:07,100 --> 01:18:09,100
Now Kazuma's hitting me!

1289
01:18:09,400 --> 01:18:10,370
Shouta-nii...

1290
01:18:12,700 --> 01:18:13,800
Wha, what's happening?

1291
01:18:20,740 --> 01:18:21,800
The world clock is...

1292
01:18:23,580 --> 01:18:24,600
going haywire.

